    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-04-17T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-04-17T23:00:00-05:00" n="369"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d369">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">600.939/307: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-04-18T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >April 18, 1939—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 3:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>191. Peiping’s 159, March 29, 3 p.m.<note n="38" xml:id="d369fn38">Not
                        printed.</note> and Department’s 83, April 5, 5 p.m. Tientsin’s despatch
                    7712 [<hi rend="italic">776</hi>], April 15th,<note n="38" xml:id="d369fn39">Not
                        printed.</note> reports that postal authorities have received instructions
                    permitting the use of parcel post facilities for transmission and delivery of
                    certain furs. The types are those in which the Fur Exporters Association is said
                    to be especially interested.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Tokyo and Chungking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
